<div class="header-band">
  <span class="header-eyebrow">The Math</span>
  <h1>What are missed calls <em>really</em> costing you?</h1>
  <p>No made-up industry stats. Drag three sliders with your own numbers and see what walks out the door when nobody answers.</p>
</div>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="calc-card fade-in">
    <div class="sliders">
      <div class="slider-row">
        <div class="slider-head">
          <label for="rTicket">What's a new customer worth to you?</label>
          <span class="slider-val" id="rTicketV">$300</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="rTicket" min="25" max="3000" step="25" value="300" aria-describedby="rTicketHint">
        <p class="slider-hint" id="rTicketHint">Think beyond the first visit — a good customer usually comes back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="slider-row">
        <div class="slider-head">
          <label for="rLeads">Calls &amp; messages you miss in a month</label>
          <span class="slider-val" id="rLeadsV">10</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="rLeads" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10" aria-describedby="rLeadsHint">
        <p class="slider-hint" id="rLeadsHint">Busy with a customer, after hours, on the other line — the ones that go to voicemail or nowhere.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="slider-row">
        <div class="slider-head">
          <label for="rClose">How many would book if answered instantly?</label>
          <span class="slider-val" id="rCloseV">30%</span>
        </div>
        <input type="range" id="rClose" min="10" max="70" step="5" value="30" aria-describedby="rCloseHint">
        <p class="slider-hint" id="rCloseHint">Your normal booking rate, applied to the people you never got to answer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="result" role="status" aria-live="polite">
      <div class="result-label">Walking out the door</div>
      <div class="result-big" id="rMonthly">$900<span>/month</span></div>
      <div class="result-year">That's <strong id="rYearly">$10,800</strong> a year — from customers who already tried to reach you.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="honesty fade-in">Your sliders, your math: missed calls × your booking rate × what a customer is worth.
    We don't pad it with "industry averages" — the honest number is convincing enough.</p>
</div>

<section class="context">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-head fade-in">
      <div class="section-label">Why It Adds Up</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">You never hear the calls you miss.</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">A missed call doesn't complain — it just books somewhere else. The customers you lose
        this way never show up in any report, which is why the leak feels invisible until you do the math above.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ctx-grid fade-in">
      <div class="ctx-cell"><h3>While you're working</h3><p>Mid-haircut, mid-appointment, mid-job — exactly when you can't pick up is when the next customer calls.</p></div>
      <div class="ctx-cell"><h3>After hours</h3><p>People search and reach out at night and on Sundays. If nothing answers, the next result on Google does.</p></div>
      <div class="ctx-cell"><h3>Voicemail isn't a safety net</h3><p>Callers who wanted an answer now rarely wait for a callback — they just dial the next place on the list.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

